The paper focuses on the relationship between internet user type and user performance when carrying out web search tasks. This involves analyzing user behavior and characteristics when carrying out simple and complex search tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is Information Retrieval (cs.IR), which deals with search engines and information retrieval systems. Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HCI) is also likely, as the study involves analyzing user behavior and performance. Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Deep Learning (cs.DL) may also be relevant, as the study may involve analyzing the language used in search queries and the use of machine learning algorithms to analyze user behavior. Finally, Cybersecurity (cs.CY) may be relevant, as the study may involve analyzing the security implications of different user types and their search behavior.
